==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tendance
<hw>Tend"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Tend</er>
to attend, and cf. <er>Attendance</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of attending or waiting; attendance.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The breath⟦br⟧
Of her sweet <qex>tendance</qex> hovering over him.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Persons in attendance; attendants.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tendence</ent>⟦br⟧
